made any friends yet.

00:20.029 --> 00:22.999
Oh, yeah. No, no, no, right
now, she's probably...

00:23.023 --> 00:25.290
Well, allowing for the
three-hour time difference,

00:25.315 --> 00:27.443
she's probably eating
spaghetti with a guy,

00:28.495 --> 00:32.216
some prep school billionaire's son, and
they're doing that, that noodle thing.

00:38.964 --> 00:41.318
Or she's studying.
Yeah, she's studying.

00:41.342 --> 00:42.819
I mean, she's really
cracking those books.

00:42.843 --> 00:45.822
Recharge? Your coffee. More?

00:45.846 --> 00:48.190
Oh, yeah. Sure.

00:51.143 --> 00:53.070
Oh, I had an uncle
who was there.

00:54.813 --> 00:56.917
- Really?
- Yeah, mmm-hmm.

00:56.941 --> 00:58.825
Then he must be... He
must be pretty old.

00:59.109 --> 01:01.703
They haven't kept prisoners
there since, like, 1963.

01:01.737 --> 01:03.632
Oh, he worked there,
in the kitchen.

01:03.656 --> 01:04.831
Oh.

01:07.034 --> 01:08.543
What?

01:08.786 --> 01:11.672
You guys didn't think he was,
like, a murderer or something?

01:12.539 --> 01:14.132
Yeah, right.

