<i>♪ Closer to free ♪</i>

02:54.016 --> 02:56.202
- Hello?
- Who's that?

02:56.226 --> 02:59.414
- Julia.
- Hey, Julia.

02:59.438 --> 03:00.989
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:01.190 --> 03:02.625
Well, it's funny.

03:02.649 --> 03:05.128
- You don't look 21.
- Anyone around?

03:05.152 --> 03:08.006
Molly, Terry? I know
it's kind of early.

03:08.030 --> 03:12.177
Well, actually, it's kind of late.
We shut down, babe.

03:12.201 --> 03:14.429
- What? Really?
- Yeah. Really?

03:14.453 --> 03:15.930
They had the hearing already?

03:15.954 --> 03:19.934
They suspended his license, and
he's got to pay some big fine.

03:19.958 --> 03:22.010
Poor old Morgan. Yeah.

03:22.377 --> 03:23.688
I didn't think they would...

03:23.712 --> 03:25.514
This is his third strike.

03:25.756 --> 03:28.558
I've tried calling him.
Maybe his machine's broken.

03:28.759 --> 03:30.435
Mmm, yeah.

03:30.761 --> 03:32.020
Have you talked to him?

03:32.095 --> 03:35.649
Yeah, he owes me 600
bucks, the bastard.

03:36.100 --> 03:37.567
Oh, boy.

03:38.060 --> 03:42.781
You know, he's probably gonna lose the
club, and what a pain in the ass,

03:42.940 --> 03:45.575
because he's not
really that bad a guy.

03:46.443 --> 03:50.122
- I know.
- Yeah, you do know, don't you?

03:52.783 --> 03:54.793
I wish that there
was something...

03:58.664 --> 03:59.840
Is he okay?

04:01.792 --> 04:03.093
No.

04:05.045 --> 04:08.399
"Right and wrong: Early childhood and
the development of a moral code."

04:08.423 --> 04:10.443
Wow, is that your topic?

04:10.467 --> 04:11.977
Maybe. Don't know yet.

04:12.386 --> 04:14.312
Something about early
childhood development.

04:14.888 --> 04:17.482
What is it they say, "Those
who can't do, teach"?

04:17.766 --> 04:20.110
Hey. Come on.

04:22.103 --> 04:23.540
I gotta go.

04:23.564 --> 04:25.907
I've got a meeting
with my committee.

04:27.359 --> 04:29.453
Have you seen my
stupid watch anywhere?

04:30.112 --> 04:31.172
Where did you leave it?

04:31.196 --> 04:32.706
I don't remember.

04:33.240 --> 04:34.583
Look for me.

04:35.284 --> 04:37.002
Maybe check around my desk.

04:39.037 --> 04:42.632
Never mind. In the
medicine cabinet.

04:43.000 --> 04:44.676
Go figure.

04:46.003 --> 04:48.096
Are you gonna be home
later on tonight?

04:48.130 --> 04:49.065
Uh...

04:49.089 --> 04:51.349
I thought I'd stop by, see Owen.

04:54.428 --> 04:56.229
I'm late.

04:57.389 --> 04:58.700
I'll see you later.

04:58.724 --> 04:59.983
Sure.

05:17.951 --> 05:19.220
I think Shelby likes me.

05:19.244 --> 05:21.588
Really, I think it's
a real possibility.

05:22.206 --> 05:24.100
I mean, did you see the way
she threw that Jell-O?

05:24.124 --> 05:27.010
Whew. Perfect aim. She
got me right in my ear.

05:29.254 --> 05:30.847
Get out of the jeep, Will.

05:31.256 --> 05:32.650
- What?
- Just get out.

05:32.674 --> 05:34.319
Get out, we're close
to your house.

05:34.343 --> 05:35.570
We're, like, two
miles from my house.

05:35.594 --> 05:37.229
It's good exercise.

05:37.930 --> 05:40.575
Hey, it's that girl,
that coffee girl...

05:40.599 --> 05:41.816
Jill.

05:42.768 --> 05:45.362
Well, this has been a
terrific friendship.

05:45.395 --> 05:47.582
You're just going to blow me off now?
Is that what's going on?

05:47.606 --> 05:49.115
Sure.

05:56.448 --> 05:59.376
Hey. You need a ride?

06:01.453 --> 06:02.963
It depends on where
you're going.

06:03.246 --> 06:08.468
Uh, well, home was my original
plan, but I'm open to suggestions.

06:14.383 --> 06:16.768
So how fast did you say
this thing could go?

06:24.017 --> 06:25.735
Hi, Morgan.

06:32.275 --> 06:34.452
I stopped by the club today,

06:34.528 --> 06:39.082
and Loren told me about them
suspending your liquor license.

06:39.199 --> 06:40.583
I'm sorry.

06:41.118 --> 06:44.212
I know you're mad at me, and you
should be, because it's my fault,

06:45.038 --> 06:47.934
and I know that I lied about my
age, but that was the only thing.

06:47.958 --> 06:49.602
I mean, that's the only
thing that I lied about.

06:49.626 --> 06:51.970
- The rest of it was...
- Forget it, all right?

06:53.046 --> 06:55.849
I heard about the fine, so I...

06:57.009 --> 07:00.312
It's not everything. I can get more.
I thought it would help.

07:01.054 --> 07:03.074
My family, we have this
checkbook for emergencies,

07:03.098 --> 07:05.525
and I thought this was
an emergency, so...

07:06.518 --> 07:07.944
Keep your money.

07:09.479 --> 07:12.750
Come on, if you pay off the fine, then
maybe you can open the club again.

07:12.774 --> 07:14.127
It's a little late
for that, Julia.

07:14.151 --> 07:15.910
No, it's not. Why
is it too late?

07:20.574 --> 07:23.511
Because your stupid little cheque
for $250 doesn't mean anything.

07:23.535 --> 07:25.596
Morgan, please, I
have to do something.

07:25.620 --> 07:26.838
Then get out of here.

07:35.047 --> 07:38.308
Yeah, that's right. I'm drunk.

07:40.969 --> 07:43.239
So your sister is coming the
day after tomorrow, huh?

07:43.263 --> 07:44.898
Mmm-hmm.

07:45.182 --> 07:47.817
When was the last time you and Meg
got to spend any time together?

07:47.893 --> 07:51.696
I went home for a few days last Christmas.
That doesn't really count.

07:51.980 --> 07:54.282
Thank you. Thank you.

07:55.025 --> 07:57.325
I guess if you were there
for longer than a week,

07:57.418 --> 07:59.603
you'd get to spend some
real quality time, huh?

08:01.198 --> 08:02.499
You found the ticket.

08:05.202 --> 08:08.421
Meg sent it. She wants me
to come home for a while.

08:08.830 --> 08:10.382
Why are you running away?

08:11.041 --> 08:12.634
I'm not running away.

08:15.170 --> 08:20.109
I'm not. I can work on my dissertation
there and spend some time with my family.

08:20.133 --> 08:21.986
I thought your family
drove you crazy.

08:22.010 --> 08:25.573
I mean, there's not one story that you tell about
them that doesn't end with "Can you believe that?"

08:25.597 --> 08:27.649
I need a change, Charlie.

08:28.517 --> 08:31.069
You're going home because
you can't have kids.

08:32.312 --> 08:34.239
My family will take care of me.

08:36.566 --> 08:39.837
- So would I.
- I wouldn't ask you to.

08:39.861 --> 08:40.797
I'm offering.

08:40.821 --> 08:44.039
Look, Charlie, we were just getting
good at this friends stuff.

08:44.408 --> 08:46.543
I don't want to get
that screwed up.

08:47.953 --> 08:50.588
Look, I haven't even
decided if I'm going.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.218
Okay.

08:58.630 --> 09:01.391
I had chem lab after
you last semester.

09:01.716 --> 09:03.476
I sat at your table.

09:04.636 --> 09:06.813
You dripped your
name on it in acid.

09:07.222 --> 09:08.857
Oh, right.

09:09.433 --> 09:11.359
Yeah, I didn't learn too
much in that class.

09:11.935 --> 09:13.278
Me neither.

09:20.527 --> 09:24.873
Rust is, is a compound
called iron oxide.

09:54.269 --> 09:55.403
Just relax.

09:57.772 --> 09:59.240
It's okay.

09:59.816 --> 10:01.409
What?

10:02.861 --> 10:04.120
Whatever.

10:17.125 --> 10:19.803
- Wait a second.
- What?

10:21.129 --> 10:23.765
- I don't have anything.
- What?

10:23.882 --> 10:25.809
I didn't bring anything.

10:28.929 --> 10:30.313
Oh.

10:32.974 --> 10:36.194
Um, well, rain check?

10:38.355 --> 10:40.698
- Yeah.
- Okay.

10:49.074 --> 10:51.677
I'm always prepared.
I'm over-prepared.

10:51.701 --> 10:53.503
How come this one time?

10:54.287 --> 10:56.140
It's amazing.

10:56.164 --> 10:59.092
You know, it's, It's too good.
I'm gonna get hit by a bus.

10:59.417 --> 11:01.636
Oh, positive attitude, Bay.

11:01.878 --> 11:05.223
What, what am I thinking? I
don't even know this girl.

11:05.257 --> 11:08.569
I mean, we, like, swapped spit.
I've never even been in her house.

11:08.593 --> 11:09.737
I don't even know
where she lives.

11:09.761 --> 11:10.780
She lives near The Presidio.

11:10.804 --> 11:13.022
She's got a little sister who knows
my little sister. She's cute.

11:13.056 --> 11:14.450
She's cute.

11:14.474 --> 11:18.152
She likes me. She wants to.
She wants to.

11:18.561 --> 11:21.290
I mean, I can get this whole
virginity thing done with.

11:21.314 --> 11:22.782
So what's the question here?

11:23.942 --> 11:25.044
Am I ready?

11:25.068 --> 11:26.462
You were ready with Kate.

11:26.486 --> 11:28.381
That's different. That's different.
I loved Kate.

11:28.405 --> 11:30.248
Bay, nobody says you
have to marry the girl.

11:35.787 --> 11:38.131
So give me some good
hometown gossip.

11:38.206 --> 11:42.186
Who's engaged, who's divorced, who's
cheating on their income taxes.

11:42.210 --> 11:46.264
Well, you're gonna find out soon enough.
You're on everybody's invite list,

11:46.965 --> 11:50.685
and Carl's taken your picture and
showing it to the guys at the ad firm.

11:50.760 --> 11:53.855
Productivity has fallen
off, oh, about 25%.

11:54.055 --> 11:57.483
Men, huh? Well, you
know, Charlie, right?

12:03.398 --> 12:07.753
So, if I go to the bathroom, are you
guys gonna talk about me behind my back?

12:07.777 --> 12:09.454
- Are you kidding?
- Absolutely.

12:17.746 --> 12:20.298
Kirsten says you've been
wonderful through all this...

12:20.832 --> 12:21.934
She does?

12:21.958 --> 12:24.395
And I'm grateful to you
too, Charlie, I really am,

12:24.419 --> 12:28.399
for being there for my sister when she
needed you and for figuring out that

12:28.423 --> 12:30.401
that's what you guys
were meant to be:

12:30.425 --> 12:31.934
Friends.

12:32.677 --> 12:35.855
Sometimes I think it takes a
while to realize that, huh?

12:39.976 --> 12:42.278
Um, I've got a crowbar.

12:44.981 --> 12:47.075
Well, not on me.

12:48.068 --> 12:49.619
What you looking for?

12:49.819 --> 12:52.121
Uh, <i>Canterbury Tales.</i>

12:52.155 --> 12:54.916
Oh, well, here, you
can borrow mine.

12:55.367 --> 12:57.794
- I just came from English.
- Hmm.

12:58.995 --> 13:01.047
Okay, now,

13:01.331 --> 13:03.726
I turned down the pages
on the dirty parts.

13:03.750 --> 13:05.176
Shh.

13:05.627 --> 13:07.595
- Thanks.
- Mmm-hmm.

13:16.513 --> 13:20.191
That's... That's a nice top.

13:22.894 --> 13:24.737
You know, I'm not
doing anything later.

13:26.356 --> 13:27.708
Oh, yeah?

13:27.732 --> 13:29.742
Yeah. No one's gonna be around.

13:30.068 --> 13:32.004
My dad, he's away, and
my mom works nights,

13:32.028 --> 13:37.083
and my brother, he won these tickets off the
radio for some stupid rodeo or something.

13:37.367 --> 13:38.969
So he's gonna take
the other kids.

13:38.993 --> 13:40.211
Ah.

13:40.620 --> 13:42.380
So no one's going to be around.

13:44.290 --> 13:46.467
You could come over about 8:00.

13:47.127 --> 13:50.096
Great. Sure, 8:00.

13:50.588 --> 13:52.056
Okay.

13:52.424 --> 13:54.684
Um, 667 Presidio...

13:54.843 --> 13:57.729
Like 666, just one more.

13:58.179 --> 13:59.323
One more. Okay.

13:59.347 --> 14:02.358
Oh, and I think you're late.

14:18.366 --> 14:19.709
Julia.

14:21.578 --> 14:22.920
Julia!

14:23.455 --> 14:24.922
What's going on, Claud?

14:25.498 --> 14:28.092
- Have you seen Julia?
- No.

14:28.126 --> 14:29.886
Well, do you, like,
know where she is?

14:30.044 --> 14:31.220
Nope.

14:31.671 --> 14:33.190
Do you know when
she's coming back?

14:33.214 --> 14:34.358
Negatory.

14:34.382 --> 14:35.526
Are you sure?

14:35.550 --> 14:38.770
Because... I really
need to talk to her.

14:39.304 --> 14:41.564
What is this, Claud? Some
big emergency or something?

14:43.141 --> 14:46.027
Well, yeah, it is.

14:49.355 --> 14:50.531
I just got my period.

14:52.984 --> 14:54.118
Oh.

14:56.988 --> 14:59.624
Okay. What have we got here?

14:59.824 --> 15:02.136
These look good. Let's
get out of here.

15:02.160 --> 15:03.628
Bailey.

15:04.579 --> 15:06.297
These are tampons.

15:06.414 --> 15:08.091
Super plus.

15:09.542 --> 15:10.885
Jeez.

15:11.503 --> 15:13.387
There sure are a lot
to choose from.

15:13.797 --> 15:17.141
These have wings. Wings?

15:18.134 --> 15:19.435
What's that about, huh?

15:19.552 --> 15:21.562
Uh, I don't think these
are right either.

15:22.972 --> 15:26.901
Scented or unscented?

15:27.018 --> 15:28.402
Which is better?

15:29.020 --> 15:30.613
You think I would know this?

15:30.855 --> 15:32.406
It's okay, Bay.

15:32.774 --> 15:35.284
Look, why don't you
just give me a minute?

15:35.360 --> 15:37.120
I mean, I can read
the boxes too.

15:37.278 --> 15:38.871
I'll figure it out.

15:38.905 --> 15:39.924
Are you sure?

15:39.948 --> 15:41.958
- Yeah.
- Great.

15:42.408 --> 15:43.918
I'll just be...

16:04.430 --> 16:06.315
What the hell are
you doing in here?

16:06.349 --> 16:08.609
Oh, um, the landlady let me in.

16:08.685 --> 16:10.788
I said I was your sister.
Pretty gullible, huh?

16:10.812 --> 16:12.697
Yeah, yeah, you are a pretty
good liar, aren't you?

16:14.274 --> 16:16.159
I could make you
dinner if you want.

16:16.693 --> 16:17.952
What did you do?

16:18.194 --> 16:20.913
You were drinking, so I...

16:21.322 --> 16:22.665
You spilled out my booze?

16:24.492 --> 16:27.137
Get out of here, just get
the hell out of here.

16:27.161 --> 16:28.754
- I'm trying to help you.
- Really?

16:28.830 --> 16:31.132
What, you think you're
gonna come over here

16:31.207 --> 16:34.645
and spill out my booze, make me dinner, and
that's gonna make everything all right?

16:34.669 --> 16:36.856
- I'm trying.
- Well, stop trying!

16:36.880 --> 16:39.807
You're just a stupid kid. You don't
know what the hell you're doing.

16:41.426 --> 16:43.895
Jeez, 15...

16:44.846 --> 16:46.856
Fifteen years old.

16:47.140 --> 16:48.242
I could've slept with you.

16:48.266 --> 16:51.527
- I said I was sorry. -Yeah? So what?
You think that counts for crap?

16:52.478 --> 16:55.406
You know, you pretend to be
grown up, but you're not.

16:55.940 --> 17:01.245
You're just a selfish little girl who likes
to play games and ruin other people's lives,

17:01.905 --> 17:04.040
and you don't know when to stop!

17:04.406 --> 17:06.626
Hey, you really want
to help me out?

17:07.035 --> 17:08.336
All right.

17:12.415 --> 17:14.300
There, clean that up.
That'll make things better.

17:24.010 --> 17:26.061
How could you
forget your wallet?

17:27.680 --> 17:29.700
God, Joe just keeps
that thing going?

17:29.724 --> 17:31.275
Isn't that kind
of a fire hazard?

17:34.145 --> 17:35.863
I called ahead.

17:38.024 --> 17:39.450
Charlie.

17:43.112 --> 17:44.664
I don't want to be your friend.

17:44.697 --> 17:45.633
What?

17:45.657 --> 17:47.583
I mean, just your friend.

17:48.743 --> 17:50.336
It's not enough.

17:50.536 --> 17:53.265
We can tell each other that that's
what we are, but we're not.

17:53.289 --> 17:54.799
We're more than that.

17:56.292 --> 17:58.302
So...

17:58.586 --> 18:00.096
Let's think big.

18:02.006 --> 18:03.432
Big?

18:06.135 --> 18:07.812
Let's think huge.

18:12.892 --> 18:15.861
Let's get married. I
want to marry you.

18:16.229 --> 18:19.240
I want you to marry me, I want
us to be married to each other.

18:22.860 --> 18:24.996
- Hello?
- I'm sorry.

18:25.446 --> 18:29.542
I... I... I'm having
trouble breathing.

18:30.201 --> 18:34.422
I just... have to... sit.

18:37.750 --> 18:41.804
Should I... I mean, do you
want me to go on? Okay.

18:42.005 --> 18:44.056
I've thought a lot about this.

18:44.298 --> 18:48.394
Well, okay, not a lot in actual terms of time,
but I've thought very intensely about it.

18:50.346 --> 18:52.273
Are you sure you're okay?

18:52.515 --> 18:54.400
Okay, so follow my logic here.

18:55.810 --> 18:58.122
Everything in your life seems
to be up in the air, right?

18:58.146 --> 19:00.239
So let's, let's pin this
one thing down: us.

19:00.732 --> 19:03.200
Let's say that we're gonna
be together forever,

19:04.318 --> 19:06.162
and, and... And I love you.

19:06.821 --> 19:10.624
I'm... I'm in love with you. I want to
spend the rest of my life with you.

19:12.577 --> 19:14.378
I should've said that first.

19:15.496 --> 19:16.839
Damn.

19:20.752 --> 19:23.763
Forget all the rest. That,
that's what it comes down to.

19:27.467 --> 19:28.851
What do you say?

19:48.488 --> 19:49.622
What?

19:57.872 --> 19:59.215
Well, don't you want to...

19:59.874 --> 20:01.717
Yeah. Yes.

20:38.538 --> 20:40.307
- Ow! Ow!
- What? What?

20:40.331 --> 20:42.466
- You're on my hair.
- Oh, sorry.

20:42.959 --> 20:44.427
- Sorry.
