40:16.965 --> 40:19.225
So how you feeling? Any cramps?

40:19.509 --> 40:20.685
Mmm-mmm.

40:23.054 --> 40:24.856
Listen, I've got an idea.

40:25.015 --> 40:27.984
How about you come upstairs and
sleep in my bed with me tonight?

40:28.727 --> 40:29.829
What?

40:29.853 --> 40:33.740
I could make popcorn, and I could read
<i>Charlotte's Web</i> to you like I used to.

40:34.357 --> 40:36.326
You really want to do that?
How come?

40:37.360 --> 40:40.163
I thought you were way too
old to share a room anymore.

40:41.364 --> 40:43.374
Who said that?

40:43.783 --> 40:45.376
I'm not too old.

40:47.787 --> 40:49.297
Come on.

40:55.962 --> 40:57.305
Hey.

40:57.339 --> 40:58.723
Hey.

41:00.842 --> 41:02.518
You look like
you've been crying.

41:02.635 --> 41:04.896
Only for about the
last 24 hours, yeah.

41:06.765 --> 41:08.608
Want to come in?

41:08.975 --> 41:10.443
No.

41:11.269 --> 41:14.656
So you came all the way over here
just to stand in the doorway?

41:18.193 --> 41:19.869
I don't know.

41:21.071 --> 41:23.247
I don't know what to do.

41:23.281 --> 41:27.877
I've been thinking about
this over and over and over.

41:29.329 --> 41:31.673
I mean, I can't marry
you, because...

41:32.123 --> 41:33.809
Well, we've been through that.

41:33.833 --> 41:37.261
And I can't go back to
Chicago, because...

41:37.504 --> 41:38.930
You're right.

41:39.089 --> 41:41.599
I would be kind of running away,

41:43.009 --> 41:46.396
but I can't just stay
where I am, because...

41:47.263 --> 41:49.023
I do need to make a change.

41:52.310 --> 41:54.195
Which leaves me...

41:54.521 --> 41:56.614
Pretty much with no options.

41:57.273 --> 41:58.950
That's not true.

41:59.317 --> 42:01.202
Name one.

42:02.153 --> 42:03.705
Move in here with me.

42:06.533 --> 42:07.750
Charlie...

42:07.867 --> 42:09.794
You need a change of scenery?
You got it.

42:10.829 --> 42:13.256
You'd be surrounded by
people who care about you.

42:13.456 --> 42:15.383
You could work on your
dissertation here.

42:15.500 --> 42:18.386
I could put a desk
in my bedroom, or...

42:19.295 --> 42:22.557
Hey, I could convert
the attic, and...

42:25.552 --> 42:27.437
What?

42:28.263 --> 42:29.772
Wow.

42:31.099 --> 42:32.442
Just...

42:35.770 --> 42:37.530
Wow, that's an amazing offer.

42:40.984 --> 42:43.035
But I don't know. I'm...

42:43.236 --> 42:47.832
I mean, what do you need this for?
I'm, like, this basket case right now.

42:50.160 --> 42:52.670
This wasn't the way things
were meant to work out.

42:53.413 --> 42:55.173
See, I, I disagree.

42:56.291 --> 42:58.384
I really disagree.

42:59.377 --> 43:01.095
Kirsten,

43:01.754 --> 43:05.475
take it from me, things never work out
the way you think they're going to.

43:06.676 --> 43:09.937
It doesn't mean that
it's not meant to be.

43:12.098 --> 43:13.524
I mean, think about it.

43:13.641 --> 43:17.445
You're 24 years old, and you can't imagine
that you're never gonna have kids.

43:17.896 --> 43:21.407
And... And... And
I'm 24 years old,

43:21.733 --> 43:24.744
and I mean, how did this happen to me?
I, I have four of them.

43:28.490 --> 43:30.333
And I love you.

43:32.243 --> 43:34.170
So why don't you share mine?

